value.value: Chemical reagent, which transforms a polar group in a molecule into a non-polar group in order to make the molecule volatile and analyzable by GC-MS.
Derivatization reagent replacing an active hydrogen by an aliphatic or aliphatic-aromatic group.
Silylation reagent replacing an active hydrogen by a silyl group.
Acylation reagent replacing an active hydrogen by a acyl (R-C=O-) group.
Halogenation reagent which can produce both silylated and halogenated derivatives.
Chiral derivatization reagent with an enatiomerically pure chiral derivatizing agent to form two diastereomeric derivatives that can be separated by gas chromatography.
Chemical reagent, which transforms an analyte so that its stability, separation, extraction, ionization efficiency and MS2 detectability are improved in LC-MS analysis.
Trimethylsilyl (TMS) reagent replacing an active hydrogen by a silyl group.
Dimethylsilyl (DMS) reagent replacing an active hydrogen by a silyl group.
Trifluoroacetyl (TFA) reagent replacing an active hydrogen by a silyl group.
Derivatization reagent replacing an active hydrogen by an aliphatic-aromatic group, e.g. a -phenyl, -tolyl, -xylyl, -naphthy, -benzyl group.
A chromophore group attached to a derivatization reagent for enhanced UB- or VIS-detectability.
A fluorophore group attached to a derivatization reagent for enhanced fluorescence or chemiluminescence detectability.
An electrophore group attached to a derivatization reagent for enhanced electrochemical detectability.
